[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: GHOST AWS Deployment and Operations Requirements
UID: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-OPERATIONS
VERSION: 0.3
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text
  AUTO_LEVELS: On
  NODE_IN_TOC: True

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 1. Scope, Evidence, and Environment Profile

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document refines the runtime-platform parent with atomic requirements for the documented current AWS deployment and the approved target remote MCP extension.

CURRENT means documented deployed behavior. TARGET means required future behavior that is not yet implementation truth.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-CAPABILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: AWS Deployment and Operations Capability
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall reproduce the documented current Phase-1 AWS deployment and shall add the target remote MCP deployment without changing the current Streamlit service unless a TARGET requirement explicitly requires an additive change.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-RUN-OPS-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-EVIDENCE-SET
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Deployment Evidence Set
STATEMENT: >>>
CURRENT requirements shall be derived from the supplied AWS deployment guide, supplied HTTPS reverse-proxy architecture, supplied ragstream-start script, and current repository deployment artifacts.

TARGET MCP requirements shall be derived from the approved deployment decisions and the applicable MCP, Claude, and ChatGPT interoperability specifications.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-EVIDENCE-CONFLICT-VISIBILITY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Deployment Evidence Conflict Visibility
STATEMENT: >>>
When supplied narrative documentation and a supplied executable deployment artifact describe different concrete commands, the requirement set shall preserve both facts explicitly and shall identify the executable command as the current executed configuration rather than silently rewriting either source.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-EVIDENCE-SET

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CURRENT-TARGET-LABELING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Current and Target Requirement Labeling
STATEMENT: >>>
Every deployment requirement shall be identifiable from its UID and title as either CURRENT or TARGET, and no TARGET MCP behavior shall be represented as already deployed.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-LOCAL-PROFILE-CONTRACT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Local Deployment Profile Contract
STATEMENT: >>>
Exact account identifiers, region, hostnames, resource identifiers, paths, commands, current configuration text, and target implementation-assigned values shall be recorded in 81_aws_deployment_profile.local.md.

Secret values shall not appear in either requirement file or the local profile.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-CAPABILITY

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 2. CURRENT AWS Network and HTTPS Entry

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The current public path is Route53 -> EC2 public IPv4 -> Security Group -> nginx -> local Docker-published Streamlit backend.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-HOST
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT EC2 Host
STATEMENT: >>>
The current deployment shall run on one Ubuntu 24.04 EC2 instance in a public subnet with a public IPv4 address and an attached IAM instance profile.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-ROOT-VOLUME
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT EC2 Root Volume Capacity
STATEMENT: >>>
The current EC2 instance shall use a root EBS volume with at least 20 GiB capacity.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-HOST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-HOST-SOFTWARE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT EC2 Host Software
STATEMENT: >>>
The current EC2 host shall have Docker, AWS CLI, nginx, and Certbot installed, and Docker and nginx shall be enabled for the documented deployment operation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-HOST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-ROUTE53-A-RECORD
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Route53 A Record
STATEMENT: >>>
The configured Route53 A record shall resolve ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com to the current EC2 public IPv4 address using the configured TTL.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-HOST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-IMDSV2-IP-READ
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT IMDSv2 Public-IP Read
STATEMENT: >>>
The current startup script shall obtain an IMDSv2 token and shall use that token to read the EC2 public IPv4 address from instance metadata.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-ROUTE53-A-RECORD

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-ROUTE53-UPSERT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Route53 Address Update
STATEMENT: >>>
The current startup script shall UPSERT the configured Route53 A record with the public IPv4 address read from IMDSv2 during each successful activation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-ROUTE53-A-RECORD

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-SG-WEB-PORTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Public Web Ports
STATEMENT: >>>
The EC2 Security Group shall allow public inbound TCP traffic on ports 80 and 443 for the documented web entry path.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-HOST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-SG-SSH-RESTRICTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT SSH Source Restriction
STATEMENT: >>>
Inbound TCP port 22 shall be restricted to the trusted administrator source and shall not be open to all internet addresses.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-HOST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-SG-NO-8501
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT No Public Streamlit Backend Port
STATEMENT: >>>
The EC2 Security Group shall contain no public inbound rule for TCP port 8501.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-SG-WEB-PORTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-NGINX-WEB-ENTRY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT nginx Web Entry
STATEMENT: >>>
nginx on the EC2 host shall be the intended public web entry point and shall select the application server block for ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-HOST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-TLS-TERMINATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT TLS Termination
STATEMENT: >>>
nginx shall terminate TLS for ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com using the Let's Encrypt certificate managed by Certbot.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-NGINX-WEB-ENTRY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-HTTP-REDIRECT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT HTTP-to-HTTPS Redirect
STATEMENT: >>>
Requests received on public port 80 shall be redirected to HTTPS on port 443 under the Certbot-managed nginx configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-TLS-TERMINATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-STREAMLIT-PROXY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Streamlit Reverse Proxy
STATEMENT: >>>
The nginx application route shall proxy to http://127.0.0.1:8501 using HTTP/1.1 and shall preserve the Host, X-Real-IP, X-Forwarded-For, X-Forwarded-Proto, Upgrade, and Connection headers required by the supplied configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-NGINX-WEB-ENTRY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-STREAMLIT-PROXY-TIMEOUT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Streamlit Proxy Read Timeout
STATEMENT: >>>
The current Streamlit nginx route shall use the documented long proxy read timeout so long-running Streamlit connections are not terminated by the reverse proxy.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-STREAMLIT-PROXY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-8501-PUBLISH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Docker Host Port 8501 Publication
STATEMENT: >>>
The current startup script shall publish host port 8501 to container port 8501 with Docker -p 8501:8501, which binds host port 8501 on all host interfaces.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-STREAMLIT-PROXY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-8501-PROTECTION-COMBINATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Port 8501 Protection Combination
STATEMENT: >>>
Direct public access to the broadly published host port 8501 shall be prevented by the Security Group prohibition on public inbound port 8501, while users access Streamlit through nginx on HTTPS port 443.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-8501-PUBLISH

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3. CURRENT Docker Image and ECR Delivery

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The current repository builds one Streamlit image and pushes it to the configured private ECR repository. Image activation on EC2 remains a separate step.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-BASE-IMAGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Docker Base Image
STATEMENT: >>>
The current Docker image shall use python:3.11-slim and /app as its working directory.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-SYSTEM-DEPS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Docker System Dependencies
STATEMENT: >>>
The current Docker build shall install build-essential and shall remove the apt package-list cache afterward.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-BASE-IMAGE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-PYTHON-DEPS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Python Dependency Installation
STATEMENT: >>>
The current Docker build shall copy requirements.txt to /app/requirements.txt and shall install the declared Python packages with pip --no-cache-dir.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-BASE-IMAGE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-PLAYWRIGHT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Playwright Chromium Installation
STATEMENT: >>>
The current repository Dockerfile shall install Playwright Chromium and its operating-system dependencies after installing requirements.txt.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-PYTHON-DEPS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-COPY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Repository Copy
STATEMENT: >>>
The current Docker build shall copy the repository build context into /app after dependency installation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-BASE-IMAGE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-STREAMLIT-CMD
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Streamlit Container Command
STATEMENT: >>>
The current image shall set PYTHONPATH=/app and STREAMLIT_SERVER_PORT=8501, expose container port 8501, and start ragstream/app/ui_streamlit.py with Streamlit listening on 0.0.0.0:8501.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-BASE-IMAGE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKERIGNORE-RUNTIME-DATA
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Runtime-Data Build Exclusions
STATEMENT: >>>
The Docker build context shall exclude data/doc_raw/ and data/chroma_db/ so current persistent document-ingestion data is not copied into the image.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOCKER-COPY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-ECR-IMAGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Private ECR Image
STATEMENT: >>>
The current deployment shall use the configured private ECR registry and ragstream-web repository with the latest image tag recorded in the local deployment profile.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CI-PUSH-TRIGGER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT CI Push Trigger
STATEMENT: >>>
The ECR workflow shall be eligible on pushes to main only when the changed paths match ragstream/**, requirements.txt, Dockerfile, or .github/workflows/deploy-to-ecr.yml.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-ECR-IMAGE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CI-DEPLOY-GATE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT CI Deployment Gate
STATEMENT: >>>
The build-and-push job shall run only for a manual workflow_dispatch event or for an eligible push whose head commit message contains [deploy].
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CI-PUSH-TRIGGER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CI-AWS-CREDENTIALS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT CI AWS Credentials
STATEMENT: >>>
GitHub Actions shall obtain the current AWS access-key ID and secret access key from the configured GitHub repository secrets and shall use them only for the current AWS CLI/ECR workflow actions.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-ECR-IMAGE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CI-ECR-SEQUENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT ECR Build and Push Sequence
STATEMENT: >>>
The current workflow shall log in to ECR, build the local image, tag it with the configured full ECR image reference, and push that tagged image.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-ECR-IMAGE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CI-NO-EC2-ACTIVATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT CI and EC2 Activation Separation
STATEMENT: >>>
A successful ECR push shall not by itself replace the running EC2 container; EC2 activation shall remain a separate manual or boot-triggered action.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CI-ECR-SEQUENCE

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 4. CURRENT EC2 Activation and Persistent Data

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The supplied executable startup script is the concrete current container-start artifact. Its two bind mounts are recorded exactly; the broader root-mount statement in the deployment guide is retained only as a documented source discrepancy.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-START-SCRIPT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT EC2 Startup Script
STATEMENT: >>>
The current EC2 deployment shall use /usr/local/bin/ragstream-start as the executable activation script.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-START-FAILFAST
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Startup Failure Semantics
STATEMENT: >>>
The current startup script shall run with set -euo pipefail and shall stop when an unhandled activation command fails.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-START-SCRIPT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-PERSISTENT-DIRS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Persistent Directory Creation
STATEMENT: >>>
The current startup script shall create /home/ubuntu/ragstream_data/doc_raw and /home/ubuntu/ragstream_data/chroma_db before starting the container.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-START-SCRIPT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-OPENAI-SSM-READ
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT OpenAI Key Retrieval
STATEMENT: >>>
The current startup script shall read the SecureString parameter /ragstream/prod/OPENAI_API_KEY from SSM Parameter Store with decryption in eu-central-1 and shall retain the returned value only as runtime process data for container injection.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-START-SCRIPT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-ECR-LOGIN-PULL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT ECR Login and Pull
STATEMENT: >>>
The current startup script shall obtain a temporary ECR login password, log Docker into the configured registry, and pull the configured latest image before replacing the application container.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-START-SCRIPT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CONTAINER-REPLACE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Streamlit Container Replacement
STATEMENT: >>>
If a Docker container named ragstream already exists, the current startup script shall remove it before starting the replacement container.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-START-SCRIPT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CONTAINER-RESTART-POLICY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Streamlit Restart Policy
STATEMENT: >>>
The current Streamlit container shall use Docker restart policy unless-stopped.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CONTAINER-REPLACE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CONTAINER-OPENAI-ENV
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT OpenAI Environment Injection
STATEMENT: >>>
The current startup script shall inject the SSM-retrieved value into the Streamlit container as OPENAI_API_KEY.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CONTAINER-REPLACE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOC-RAW-BIND-MOUNT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Raw-Document Bind Mount
STATEMENT: >>>
The current executed Docker command shall bind /home/ubuntu/ragstream_data/doc_raw to /app/data/doc_raw in the Streamlit container.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CONTAINER-REPLACE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CHROMA-BIND-MOUNT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Chroma Bind Mount
STATEMENT: >>>
The current executed Docker command shall bind /home/ubuntu/ragstream_data/chroma_db to /app/data/chroma_db in the Streamlit container.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CONTAINER-REPLACE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-NO-WHOLE-DATA-MOUNT-CLAIM
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Exact Mount Claim
STATEMENT: >>>
The current requirement set shall not claim that the executed startup command mounts the entire /home/ubuntu/ragstream_data root to /app/data, because the supplied executable script mounts only the doc_raw and chroma_db subtrees.

The deployment guide's broader root-mount description shall remain recorded as a source discrepancy in the local profile.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOC-RAW-BIND-MOUNT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-PERSISTENCE-SURVIVES-REPLACE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Persistence Across Container Replacement
STATEMENT: >>>
Files written under /app/data/doc_raw and /app/data/chroma_db shall remain on the EC2/EBS filesystem when the Streamlit container or Docker image is replaced.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DOC-RAW-BIND-MOUNT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-IMAGE-PRUNE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Docker Image Pruning
STATEMENT: >>>
After the container start and Route53 update commands, the current startup script shall invoke Docker image pruning for unused images and shall not fail the activation solely because pruning fails.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-START-SCRIPT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-SYSTEMD-UNIT
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT systemd Activation Unit
STATEMENT: >>>
The current EC2 host shall use /etc/systemd/system/ragstream.service as a oneshot unit that executes /usr/local/bin/ragstream-start after network-online.target and docker.service and remains active after the script exits successfully.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-START-SCRIPT

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-MANUAL-ACTIVATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Manual Activation Command
STATEMENT: >>>
After a successful image push, the current preferred activation command shall be sudo /usr/local/bin/ragstream-start; rebooting the EC2 instance may alternatively trigger the enabled systemd unit.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-SYSTEMD-UNIT

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 5. CURRENT IAM, Secret Handling, Verification, and Non-Goals

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section contains only the IAM permissions, secret boundaries, operational checks, and explicit Phase-1 exclusions documented by the supplied deployment evidence.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-ROLE-PERMISSIONS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT EC2 Role Permissions
STATEMENT: >>>
The EC2 instance profile shall permit the startup script to pull the configured ECR image, decrypt and read /ragstream/prod/OPENAI_API_KEY, and change the configured Route53 hosted-zone record.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-HOST

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-NO-EC2-ACCESS-KEY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT No Static AWS Access Key on EC2
STATEMENT: >>>
The EC2 activation path shall use the attached instance role and shall not require an AWS access-key ID or secret access key stored on the instance.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-EC2-ROLE-PERMISSIONS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-SECRET-NOT-IN-IMAGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Secret Exclusion from Image
STATEMENT: >>>
The OpenAI API key value and GitHub AWS secret values shall not be copied into the Docker image or stored in version-controlled deployment files.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-OPENAI-SSM-READ

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-PUBLIC-ENDPOINT-CHECK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Public Endpoint Verification
STATEMENT: >>>
Current deployment verification shall confirm that https://ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com responds through nginx and that users are not required to specify port 8501.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-CONTAINER-CHECK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Container Verification
STATEMENT: >>>
Current deployment verification shall confirm that the ragstream container is running with the expected image, restart policy, port publication, two documented bind mounts, and a non-empty OPENAI_API_KEY environment value without printing or otherwise disclosing the secret value.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-PUBLIC-ENDPOINT-CHECK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-NGINX-CERTBOT-CHECK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT nginx and Certificate Verification
STATEMENT: >>>
Current deployment verification shall include nginx configuration validation, nginx service status, and a Certbot renewal dry run.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-PUBLIC-ENDPOINT-CHECK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-DNS-CHECK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT DNS Verification
STATEMENT: >>>
Current deployment verification shall confirm that ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com resolves to the EC2 public IPv4 address written by the startup script.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-PUBLIC-ENDPOINT-CHECK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-PERSISTENCE-CHECK
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Ingestion Persistence Verification
STATEMENT: >>>
Current deployment verification shall confirm that uploaded raw files appear under the host doc_raw subtree and that Chroma data and file_manifest.json appear under the host chroma_db project subtree.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-CUR-PUBLIC-ENDPOINT-CHECK

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-CUR-PHASE1-NONGOALS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: CURRENT Phase-1 Non-Goals
STATEMENT: >>>
The current AWS deployment shall not be represented as providing Cognito-triggered instance start, an Application Load Balancer, CloudFront as an always-on front door, autoscaling, multi-instance operation, multi-tenant hardening, or public backend ports other than 80 and 443.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-CAPABILITY

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 6. TARGET MCP Hosting and Network Topology

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The initial MCP service is additive: same EC2, separate container, same hostname and certificate, exact /mcp public route, and loopback-only backend publication.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SAME-EC2
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP on Existing EC2
STATEMENT: >>>
The initial remote MCP service shall run on the same EC2 instance as the current Streamlit deployment.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-DEPLOYMENT-CAPABILITY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Separate MCP Container
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP service shall run in a Docker container separate from the current ragstream Streamlit container.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SAME-EC2

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PUBLIC-URL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Public URL
STATEMENT: >>>
The externally configured MCP server URL shall be exactly https://ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com/mcp.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SAME-EC2

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-NGINX-ROUTE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Exact nginx MCP Route
STATEMENT: >>>
The Certbot-managed HTTPS server block for ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com shall contain an exact /mcp route that proxies to the local MCP backend without changing the existing Streamlit location / route.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PUBLIC-URL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-LOOPBACK-BIND
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Loopback Host Binding
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP container port 8000 shall be published only as 127.0.0.1:8000 on the EC2 host and shall not be bound to the EC2 public interfaces.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-NO-SG-8000
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET No Public MCP Backend Port
STATEMENT: >>>
The EC2 Security Group shall contain no inbound rule for TCP port 8000.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-LOOPBACK-BIND

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-EXTERNAL-HTTPS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET External HTTPS Only
STATEMENT: >>>
Claude and ChatGPT shall reach the MCP service only over HTTPS port 443 through nginx; they shall never connect directly to port 8000 or to an unencrypted public MCP URL.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PUBLIC-URL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-INTERNAL-HTTP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Local Proxy Hop
STATEMENT: >>>
The nginx-to-MCP backend hop shall use HTTP only over EC2 loopback at http://127.0.0.1:8000 because public TLS terminates at nginx.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-LOOPBACK-BIND

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-INDEPENDENT-ACTIVATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Independent MCP Activation
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP container shall have an activation mechanism independent of the current /usr/local/bin/ragstream-start behavior so MCP deployment or restart does not replace or reconfigure the current Streamlit container.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-IMAGE-RECORD
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Image Reference Recording
STATEMENT: >>>
The exact image reference used by the MCP container shall be recorded in the local deployment profile before deployment.

This requirement shall not predetermine whether the MCP implementation uses the current application image or a separate image.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-NO-PROJECT-MOUNTS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET No Project or Memory Data Mounts
STATEMENT: >>>
The initial MCP container shall not mount the current doc_raw, chroma_db, memory, or other project-persistence directories because the approved initial ghost_engineer_prompt tool requires only prompt-processing code and configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-ECR-DELIVERY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Controlled MCP Image Delivery
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP runtime image shall be built by GitHub Actions and pushed to a private Amazon ECR repository through the same controlled deployment gate used by the current deployment: manual workflow dispatch or an eligible main-branch push whose head commit message contains [deploy].

The exact Dockerfile, workflow path, ECR repository, and image reference shall be recorded in the local deployment profile before deployment.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-ACTIVATION-SEQUENCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Activation Sequence
STATEMENT: >>>
The independent MCP activation mechanism shall authenticate Docker to ECR through the EC2 instance role, pull the recorded MCP image, remove only a pre-existing MCP container with the recorded container name, and start the replacement MCP container with the approved loopback port publication and runtime configuration.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-INDEPENDENT-ACTIVATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-RESTART-POLICY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Container Restart Policy
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP container shall use the Docker restart policy unless-stopped, matching the current Streamlit container's restart behavior.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-ACTIVATION-SEQUENCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SYSTEMD-ACTIVATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Boot Activation
STATEMENT: >>>
The EC2 host shall use a systemd unit separate from ragstream.service to invoke the independent MCP activation mechanism after network-online.target and docker.service during instance boot.

The exact unit and activation paths shall be recorded in the local deployment profile before installation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-INDEPENDENT-ACTIVATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SSM-INJECTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Runtime Secret Injection
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP activation mechanism shall read the existing OpenAI API key and every secret required by the selected OAuth realization from recorded SSM Parameter Store references or from the selected external authorization provider at runtime.

Secret values shall not be embedded in the image, activation artifact, systemd unit, nginx configuration, repository, or local deployment profile.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-INDEPENDENT-ACTIVATION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-EC2-ROLE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP EC2 Role Permissions
STATEMENT: >>>
The existing EC2 instance role shall be extended only as required to pull the recorded MCP image and read the exact SSM parameters used by the MCP activation mechanism.

The MCP deployment shall not require a static AWS access-key ID or secret access key on EC2.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SSM-INJECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-DNS-REUSE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Existing DNS Record Reuse
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP endpoint shall reuse the existing ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com Route53 A record and shall not require a second public DNS record because the MCP route is hosted under the existing application hostname.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PUBLIC-URL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-CERTIFICATE-REUSE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Existing TLS Certificate Reuse
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP endpoint shall use the existing Certbot-managed TLS certificate for ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com through the existing nginx HTTPS server block and shall not terminate public TLS inside the MCP container.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PUBLIC-URL

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 7. TARGET MCP Streamable HTTP and nginx Proxy Contract

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The public endpoint uses the MCP Streamable HTTP transport. nginx remains the public TLS boundary and must preserve the protocol and authorization information required by the backend.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-STREAMABLE-HTTP
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Streamable HTTP Transport
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP server shall implement the MCP Streamable HTTP transport at the single /mcp endpoint.

HTTP POST shall process MCP JSON-RPC messages. HTTP GET shall either open the transport's server-to-client event stream or return HTTP 405 Method Not Allowed when the server does not offer a standalone event stream.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-NGINX-ROUTE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-JSONRPC-UTF8
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP JSON-RPC Encoding
STATEMENT: >>>
MCP protocol messages shall use JSON-RPC and UTF-8 encoding in accordance with the negotiated MCP protocol version.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-STREAMABLE-HTTP

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PROTOCOL-HANDSHAKE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Initialization Handshake
STATEMENT: >>>
The endpoint shall complete initialize and notifications/initialized before accepting normal tool discovery and invocation for a client session.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-STREAMABLE-HTTP

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-TOOL-PROTOCOL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Tool Operations
STATEMENT: >>>
The endpoint shall support tools/list and tools/call for the single ghost_engineer_prompt tool defined by 73_mcp_interface.sdoc.

The endpoint shall not advertise a standalone PreProcessing tool, a standalone A2 tool, or any additional GHOST capability under the initial requirement set.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-STREAMABLE-HTTP

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-ORIGIN-VALIDATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Origin Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP HTTP server shall validate every present Origin header against an explicitly configured allowlist and shall return HTTP 403 when a present Origin is not allowed.

Client-origin values shall be recorded in the local profile only after they are established by provider documentation or real acceptance testing.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-STREAMABLE-HTTP

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PROXY-HEADERS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Proxy Headers
STATEMENT: >>>
The nginx /mcp route shall preserve Host, X-Real-IP, X-Forwarded-For, X-Forwarded-Proto, Authorization, Origin, Content-Type, Accept, MCP-Protocol-Version, MCP-Session-Id, and Last-Event-ID information required by the backend to process authenticated MCP requests correctly.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-NGINX-ROUTE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PROXY-STREAMING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Proxy Streaming Behavior
STATEMENT: >>>
The nginx /mcp route shall disable response buffering and caching and shall use proxy timeouts that permit the Streamable HTTP response mode used by the MCP server.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-NGINX-ROUTE

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 8. TARGET MCP OAuth Interoperability

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP server is the OAuth protected resource. The authorization-server implementation or provider is not fixed by this requirement set; the selected solution must satisfy the discovery, PKCE, resource-binding, refresh, secret-storage, and real-client acceptance requirements below.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-OAUTH-PROTECTED-RESOURCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET OAuth-Protected MCP Resource
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP endpoint shall act as an OAuth-protected resource server for HTTP transport and shall require a valid access token before processing tool discovery or tool invocation.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PUBLIC-URL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-RESOURCE-METADATA
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Protected Resource Metadata
STATEMENT: >>>
The deployment shall publish OAuth Protected Resource Metadata at https://ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com/.well-known/oauth-protected-resource/mcp for the canonical MCP resource https://ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com/mcp and shall identify at least one authorization server used by the clients.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-OAUTH-PROTECTED-RESOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-AUTH-SERVER-DISCOVERY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Authorization-Server Discovery
STATEMENT: >>>
The selected authorization server shall publish OAuth Authorization Server Metadata or OpenID Connect discovery metadata containing the endpoints and capabilities required by the MCP clients.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-RESOURCE-METADATA

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-401-CHALLENGE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Unauthenticated MCP Challenge
STATEMENT: >>>
An unauthenticated request to /mcp shall return HTTP 401 and shall provide the protected-resource metadata location through the standards-defined discovery mechanism used by the MCP client.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-RESOURCE-METADATA

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-BEARER-HEADER
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Bearer-Token Header
STATEMENT: >>>
Authenticated MCP requests shall carry the access token in the HTTP Authorization Bearer header, and the deployment shall not accept access tokens in the request URI query string.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-OAUTH-PROTECTED-RESOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-RESOURCE-INDICATOR
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Resource Indicator
STATEMENT: >>>
The OAuth authorization and token flow shall bind issued access tokens to the canonical MCP resource identifier so the MCP server can validate that each token was issued for this endpoint.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-OAUTH-PROTECTED-RESOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-TOKEN-VALIDATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Access-Token Validation
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP server shall reject missing, expired, invalid, wrongly scoped, or wrong-audience access tokens before executing a tool.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-OAUTH-PROTECTED-RESOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PKCE-S256
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET OAuth PKCE S256
STATEMENT: >>>
The authorization-code flow used by MCP clients shall support PKCE with the S256 code-challenge method and shall advertise that capability in authorization-server metadata.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-AUTH-SERVER-DISCOVERY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-AUTH-HTTPS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET OAuth HTTPS Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
Authorization-server endpoints and non-localhost redirect URIs used by the remote MCP connection shall use HTTPS.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-AUTH-SERVER-DISCOVERY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-REFRESH-CONNECTION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Refreshable Client Connection
STATEMENT: >>>
The authorization configuration shall issue and accept refresh tokens in the manner required by the selected Claude and ChatGPT client flows so an authorized connection can remain usable after the initial access token expires.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-AUTH-SERVER-DISCOVERY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-OFFLINE-ACCESS-METADATA
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET ChatGPT Refresh Metadata
STATEMENT: >>>
When the selected authorization provider uses offline_access to request refresh tokens, its discovery metadata shall advertise offline_access and the ChatGPT connection shall request it.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-REFRESH-CONNECTION

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-CLIENT-REGISTRATION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Client Registration Compatibility
STATEMENT: >>>
The selected client-registration mechanism shall be one supported by the configured Claude connector and one accepted by the configured ChatGPT custom app.

The exact mechanism, client identifiers, client-secret use, and redirect URIs shall be recorded in the local profile only after client configuration or acceptance testing establishes them.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-AUTH-SERVER-DISCOVERY

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-AUTH-SECRETS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET OAuth Secret Storage
STATEMENT: >>>
OAuth client secrets, signing or validation secrets, and refresh-token storage credentials required by the selected authorization implementation shall be held in the selected AWS or authorization-provider secret store and shall not be hard-coded into the repository, Dockerfile, image, nginx configuration, or local profile.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-OAUTH-PROTECTED-RESOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-NO-TOKEN-PASSTHROUGH
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET No MCP Token Passthrough
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP access token received from Claude or ChatGPT shall be used only to authorize the MCP request and shall not be forwarded to OpenAI or any other downstream API.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-OAUTH-PROTECTED-RESOURCE

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 9. TARGET MCP Tool and Existing-Code Boundary

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section defines only the deployment-facing realization of the single ghost_engineer_prompt tool. The external tool contract remains owned by 73_mcp_interface.sdoc. The internal functional semantics of deterministic prompt construction and A2 remain owned by 30_preprocessing_prompt_functions.sdoc and the existing Python implementation.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PROMPT-ENGINEERING-TOOL
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Single Prompt-Engineering MCP Tool
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP server shall deploy exactly the single ghost_engineer_prompt tool defined by 73_mcp_interface.sdoc.

For each accepted invocation, the adapter shall create a fresh request-isolated SuperPrompt, invoke the existing deterministic preprocess(...) prompt-construction function, then invoke the existing A2PromptShaper LLM path on the same SuperPrompt, and return the post-A2 engineered prompt through the MCP result contract.

The adapter shall not invoke AppController.preprocess(), ActiveBrief discovery, ActiveBrief relation classification, retrieval, memory, or any other GHOST pipeline stage.

Deterministic PreProcessing and A2 shall remain internal sequential stages of this one tool and shall not be advertised as separate MCP tools.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-TOOL-PROTOCOL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-OPENAI-KEY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP OpenAI Key Injection
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP container shall receive the existing OpenAI API key from /ragstream/prod/OPENAI_API_KEY at runtime for the A2 execution inside ghost_engineer_prompt.

The deterministic prompt-construction step preceding A2 shall not call an LLM.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PROMPT-ENGINEERING-TOOL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-CONFIG-PACKAGING
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Prompt Configuration Packaging
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP runtime image shall contain the existing prompt schema, A2 agent configuration, option catalogs, and Python modules required by the single approved ghost_engineer_prompt execution path.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PROMPT-ENGINEERING-TOOL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-NO-EXTRA-TOOLS
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET No Additional MCP Tools
STATEMENT: >>>
The initial tools/list result shall contain exactly ghost_engineer_prompt and shall contain no standalone PreProcessing tool, standalone A2 tool, or additional GHOST tool.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-TOOL-PROTOCOL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-RUNTIME-DEPENDENCY
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Runtime Dependency Declaration
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP server library and exact deployed version shall be declared in the build dependency set and recorded in the local deployment profile before the MCP image is built and accepted.

The requirement set shall not prescribe an unverified library version.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER

[[/SECTION]]

[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 10. TARGET MCP Deployment Completion and Acceptance

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
No target value is promoted merely because it appears in this specification. Promotion requires exact local-profile values and passed public-endpoint, OAuth, client, protocol, scope, and non-regression tests.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-RUNTIME-VALUES
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Runtime Value Recording
STATEMENT: >>>
Before deployment, the local profile shall record the exact MCP image reference, container name, container entry command, MCP server library and version, activation artifact paths, authorization-server issuer, authorization metadata URL, required scopes, accepted client origins, and client registration values actually used.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SEPARATE-CONTAINER

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-CURRENT-ROUTE-REGRESSION
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Current Streamlit Route Regression Check
STATEMENT: >>>
After MCP deployment, https://ragstream.rusbehabtahi.com shall continue to serve the current Streamlit application through the existing nginx root route.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-NGINX-ROUTE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-NETWORK-ACCEPTANCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Network Acceptance
STATEMENT: >>>
MCP deployment acceptance shall confirm that /mcp is reachable over HTTPS port 443, that host port 8000 listens only on 127.0.0.1, and that the Security Group has no inbound rule for port 8000.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PUBLIC-URL

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-AUTH-DISCOVERY-ACCEPTANCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET OAuth Discovery Acceptance
STATEMENT: >>>
MCP deployment acceptance shall confirm that an unauthenticated /mcp request receives the required authorization challenge and that protected-resource and authorization-server discovery documents resolve to the configured canonical values.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-RESOURCE-METADATA

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-CLAUDE-ACCEPTANCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET Claude Client Acceptance
STATEMENT: >>>
The target shall not be promoted to CURRENT until Claude can add the remote MCP server, complete OAuth authorization, discover ghost_engineer_prompt as the sole GHOST tool, invoke it successfully, receive the post-A2 engineered prompt, and continue after an access-token refresh.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-OAUTH-PROTECTED-RESOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-CHATGPT-ACCEPTANCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET ChatGPT Client Acceptance
STATEMENT: >>>
The target shall not be promoted to CURRENT until the owner's ChatGPT web account can create and enable the custom MCP plugin, complete OAuth authorization, discover ghost_engineer_prompt as the sole GHOST tool, invoke it successfully, receive the post-A2 engineered prompt in the same conversation, and continue after an access-token refresh.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-OAUTH-PROTECTED-RESOURCE

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PROTOCOL-ACCEPTANCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Protocol Acceptance
STATEMENT: >>>
MCP protocol acceptance shall complete initialize, notifications/initialized, tools/list, and one successful tools/call for ghost_engineer_prompt through the public HTTPS URL.

The returned result shall contain the engineered prompt produced only after the internal deterministic prompt-construction step and A2 execution have completed.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-STREAMABLE-HTTP

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SCOPE-ACCEPTANCE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Scope Acceptance
STATEMENT: >>>
MCP acceptance shall verify that no document, Chroma, memory, GUI, or other project data mount is attached to the initial MCP container and that no additional GHOST tool is advertised.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-NO-PROJECT-MOUNTS

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-PROMOTION-GATE
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: TARGET MCP Status Promotion Gate
STATEMENT: >>>
The MCP requirements shall remain TARGET until the implementation exists on the EC2 instance and all network, OAuth discovery, Claude, ChatGPT, protocol, tool-scope, and Streamlit-regression acceptance requirements pass.
<<<
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: GHOST-AWS-TGT-MCP-SAME-EC2

[[/SECTION]]
